headline: Charles Sporck, an Early Champion of Moving Microchip Manufacturing to Asia, Dies at 96
summary: He argued that offshoring allowed the U.S. semiconductor industry to create more high-paying jobs at home.

headline: Charles Sporck, Who Pioneered Offshoring of Microchip Production, Dies at 96
summary: He argued that moving manufacturing allowed the U.S. semiconductor industry to create more high-paying jobs at home. “We beat the Japanese,” he said.
